The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  The benchmark  FTSE MIB Index  gained 349.50, or 1.7 percent,
to 21,578.48 in Milan.  Banca Carige SpA  (CRG IM): The Genoa, Italy-based bank said
nine-month net profit fell 33 percent to 120.7 million euros
($166.9 million). Shares were unchanged at 1.67 euros.  Banca Popolare di Milano Scrl  (PMI IM): The Milan-based
cooperative bank said third-quarter profit fell 34 percent to
37.7 million euros on lower revenue and higher costs. The stock
gained 2 cents, or 0.6 percent, to 3.25 euros.  Mediaset SpA  (MS IM): The broadcaster owned by Italian
Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi posted a loss of 49 million
euros in the third quarter on charges related to investments.
The company today reiterated its forecast of an increase in
full-year net income. Shares rose 16 cents, or 3 percent, to
5.41 euros.  UniCredit SpA  (UCG IM): Italyâ€™s biggest bank said third-
quarter profit declined 15 percent after lower trading income
outweighed a drop in bad-loan provisions. Net income fell to 334
million euros from 394 million euros a year earlier, the Milan-
based lender said. That missed the 388 million-euro average
estimate of 19 analysts surveyed by Bloomberg. The shares rose
1.2 percent to 1.82 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
